    quiz: [{ question: "A patient on levetiracetam (Keppra) tells the nurse they want to stop taking the medication because it makes them irritable and angry. What is the priority response?", options: ["Agree and tell them to stop the medication immediately", "Educate that abrupt discontinuation can cause status epilepticus and report the behavioral concerns to the provider", "Suggest taking the medication every other day instead", "Tell them irritability is not a known side effect and to continue as prescribed"], correct: 1, rationale: "Behavioral changes including irritability and aggression (Keppra rage) are well-documented side effects of levetiracetam. However, abrupt discontinuation of any antiepileptic can trigger rebound seizures or life-threatening status epilepticus. The priority is to validate the concern, educate on the danger of abrupt discontinuation, and report to the provider for evaluation and possible medication adjustment or tapering." }]
